ğŸš¨ GOTCHAS TO AVOID
1. Secret Leaks
bash
# CRITICAL: Verify .gitignore is working
git check-ignore -v .env *.key credentials.json
# If not caught, add to .gitignore and commit
2. Misconfigured CI/CD
bash
# Test the workflow locally before merging
# Check .github/workflows/security-ci.yml syntax
yamllint .github/workflows/security-ci.yml
3. Missing CODEOWNERS
bash
# Verify CODEOWNERS syntax
cat .github/CODEOWNERS | grep @ | head -5
# Should see: * @team/security-team @team/maintainers
4. Broken Links in Markdown
bash
# Check for typos in file references
grep -r "CONTRIBUTING.md" . --include="*.md" | head -5
# All should point to real files
